<image 1> Which of the following is the most accurate statement of the cartoonist's meaning? 

A. World War I is the crime of the ages
B. ALl nations involved in World War I at its outbreak are to blame for it
C. Russia and Austria are blamed unfairly
D. The nations of Europe are blaming one another
E. War is a terrible crime

The most accurate statement of the cartoonist's meaning is:

D. The nations of Europe are blaming one another

The cartoon depicts various European nations pointing fingers at each other, suggesting that they are all trying to shift the blame for the outbreak of World War I. The title "The Crime of the Ages—Who Did It?" further emphasizes this idea of mutual accusation among the nations involved.
